<br>
The reception we received was largely positive.  We tried our best to show the scientific views of nuclear energy which I and most of us here believe to be most accurate.  Of course, I tried to impart some skepticism as should be with any technology or industry.  Its just when it becomes a conspiracy theorist mentality that it gets dangerous and out of control.  No source of energy is without some cost and we need to point out the impact to the environment honestly.  I believe if we are to win, we must be truthful and not resort to deception.<br>
<br>
Additionally, we had sponsored a scholarship essay contest to try and get students to learn about nuclear energy.  The contest was actually quite successful.  This is encouraging news as it tells us that the younger generation tends to be more supportive of nuclear energy.  When I spoke with them, many did not know of Three Mile Island and some not even Chernobyl.  This is ancient history to them, events at about the time or before they were born.  Right now they see rolling blackouts and rising energy costs.  Nuclear energy, I and many others believe, will provide a clean solution to a serious problem and the next generation tends to agree. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_yingyang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orion Commander</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 6:45:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  presentations about nuclear issues</span><hr size=1> Maybe this should be continued in the forum about non-space nuclear energy issues?<br>
