<br>
 So what's the stance on breeders? I know they're out of fashion (maybe the best way to describe them since it's not really &quot;outlawed&quot; in the US)<br>
 Other nations are looking at them, though nobody's got one operating yet.<br>
 Is this only funding &amp; political problems, or are there big technical hurdles?<br>
Is it correct to say that breeders could eat up spent fuel (being a big part of nuclear waste)? the problem pointed to here is the output from breders is weapons-usable Pu, but we here like to burn this stuff up by the tens of tons...<br>
 MOX is another option, which faces more political &amp; social problems than techniccal too. Take the Pu from breeders, make MOX, and run it through another fuel cycle. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_yingyang.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/27/02 2:01:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mauk2>Mauk2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 7:42:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: presentations about nuclear issues</span><hr size=1> Nuclaeon:  Welcome to the fold!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
